Package cli

Class CLIParametersUpdateVDict

java.lang.Object
cli.CLIParametersUpdateVDict
All Implemented Interfaces:
CLIParameters
public final class CLIParametersUpdateVDict
extends java.lang.Object
implements CLIParameters
Parses command line interface arguments for the `MUSIAL updateVDict` module.

Used to parse and validate passed command line options or print help information to the user. Parsed arguments are stored to be accessible for other utility of the tool.

Since:
2.0
Version:
2.1
Author:
Simon Hackl

    • features

      public final java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentSkipListMap<java.lang.String,​FeatureEntry> features
      ConcurrentSkipListMap of String, File pairs. Each key specifies one feature on the passed reference `FASTA` to be analyzed. Each assigned value points to an optional `PDB` file per feature and induces the analysis variants allocated to the protein structure; values are expected to be `null` or `""` if variant to protein structure allocation shall not be run.

  • Constructor Details

    • CLIParametersUpdateVDict

      public CLIParametersUpdateVDict​(java.lang.String[] args) throws MusialCLException, MusialIOException, MusialBioException, MusialIntegrityException
      Constructor of the CLIParametersUpdateVDict class.

      Used to parse and validate command line interface input. Parsed arguments are stored - and accessible by other utility - via class properties.

      Parameters:
      args - String Array containing the command line arguments.
      Throws:
      MusialCLException - If any error occurs during parsing or validating an MusialCLException is thrown.
      MusialIOException - If any error occurs during input file validation.
      MusialBioException - If any bioinformatics algorithmic procedure applied during updating fails.
      MusialIntegrityException - If any feature to add during updating yields wrong coordinates.

  • Method Details

    • addSample

      private void addSample​(java.lang.String name, java.io.File vcfFile, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> annotations) throws MusialIOException
      Initializes a SampleEntry object with the specified parameters and adds it to the features list.
      Parameters:
      name - String; The internal name to use for the sample.
      vcfFile - File object pointing to a .vcf format file.
      annotations - HashMap of String key/pair values; sample meta information.
      Throws:
      MusialIOException - If the specified .vcf file does not exist or can not be accessed.

    • addFeature

      private void addFeature​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String featureName, java.io.File pdbFile, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> annotations) throws MusialIOException, MusialIntegrityException, MusialBioException
      Initializes a FeatureEntry object with the specified parameters and adds it to the features list.
      Parameters:
      name - String; The internal name to use for the feature.
      featureName - String; The value of the NAME attribute in the specified .gff format reference annotation to match the feature from.
      pdbFile - File; Optional object pointing to a .pdb format file yielding a protein structure derived for the (gene) feature.
      annotations - HashMap of String key/pair values; feature meta information.
      Throws:
      MusialIOException - If the specified .gff reference annotation or .pdb protein file can not be read.
      MusialBioException - If the initialization of the FeatureEntry fails.
      MusialIntegrityException - If the specified feature is not found or parsed multiple times from the reference annotation.
